; Dungeon — level 1, static layer (structure and fixtures).
; One character per cell; every row must be the same width.
; Lines starting with ';' and blank lines are ignored.
;
;   #  solid rock          .  floor
;   P  party start         D  dusty floor (air turbidity 1)
;   T  wall torch sconce   F  fire brazier (blocks movement)
;
; Grid glyphs are never lowercase: lines starting with a lowercase letter
; are records. "textures" records declare the level's surface texture
; palette — the game loads only the sets named here (each needs its worn
; block meshes baked, see ModelBaker.cpp); "decoration" records are static
; entities (see Entity.h for the format), e.g.
;   decoration banner 4 2 north
; Dynamic content — monsters, items, buttons — lives in level1.ent.

textures wall wall_brick wall_stone wall_moss
textures floor floor_slabs floor_cobble
textures ceiling ceiling_rough ceiling_cracked
;
; 32x32 layout (4x the old map): a start room (NW) opening onto a great
; pillared hall (N), a dusty fountain hall (centre), a tomb crypt (W), a
; dusty cavern (SW), a treasure vault (S) and gallery/chambers (E/SE), all
; tied together by a looping corridor network. The fountain hall and cavern
; are dust-heavy showcases; the serpent pillar auto-spawns two cells south
; of the start.
